w:r.w:t: 5g run normally takes 10 to 15 hours, now much longer.
Analysis of plans from good and bad runs showed that the duration and physical IO were almost exactly doubled.
The Execution plans were basically the same.
Why? It eventually transpired that the developers had made small changes (addition of a few columns here or there). But nothing that would explain this degradation.

Eventually figured out that the tables were not compressed. But, were they supposed to be? We could not see how the tables used to be, but by discussing with developers it emerged that the tables were supposed to be compressed.
Normally, in Axiom, when they make a change to the data model, the data is copied forward in to new tables, and the old tables are deleted. There is also archiving at that point.
So, even if tables are uncompressed, the data is archived.
solution : run archiving and compress major tables.
Today's run has done a lot more phys IO - 1,128 GB compared to only 364 GB previously.
